<item>
            <title>[PIG-2795] Fix test cases that generate pig scripts with &quot;load &quot; + pathStr to encode &quot;\&quot; in the path</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2795</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Pig reads &quot;\&quot; as an escape character in pig scripts &amp;#8211; but Windows paths natively contain \.  When we formulate pig queries that should be read through the parser with file paths, we should call encodeEscape first to handle paths generated on Windows.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12597862">PIG-2795</key>
            <summary>Fix test cases that generate pig scripts with &quot;load &quot; + pathStr to encode &quot;\&quot; in the path</summary>
